To: comp.lang.scheme
Subject: [announce] Nausicaa/Libxml2 --- tag 0.1b0

		      Nausicaa/Libxml2
		      ================

Nausicaa/Libxml2 is  a distribution of  Scheme libraries for
R6RS  Scheme implementations; it  provides bindings  for the
Libxml2 C  language library, the  XML toolkit for  the GNOME
project.   It  is built  upon  the Nausicaa/Scheme  package,
making use of its foreign-functions interface.

  The package  works with  Ikarus, Mosh and  Ypsilon Scheme;
Larceny Scheme is not  supported.  The package supports only
GNU+Linux systems.

  The  latest  release  of  the  Nausicaa/Libxml2  package  is
available at:

     <http://github.com/marcomaggi/nausicaa/downloads>

the home page of the Nausicaa project is at:

	<http://marcomaggi.github.com/nausicaa.html>

development takes place at:

    <http://github.com/marcomaggi/nausicaa/tree/master>

the documentation is available on line:

   <http://marcomaggi.github.com/docs/nausicaa-Libxml2.html>

Libxml2 is available here:

		   <http://xmlsoft.org/>


Notes for --- tag 0.1b0
------------------------------

* It has been tested with Libxml2 version 2.7.6.

* Requires Nausicaa/Scheme version 0.1a11+.

* The macros  of (xml libxml2  structs) cannot be  used with
  Ypsilon because of Ypsilon's hygiene problems.



